Fixed _communicate func to make sure it supports all server responses

By default, we expect the server response to be a dictionary (JSON response). If not, we consider the return as data response (string). If the response is an emtpy dict, an empty string or a None value we consider the response as an invalid one.

Also, all calls to urllib have been updated to make sure that this code works both in Python 2 and 3.

NOTE: I  have used try/except fallback system to use proper urllib classes depending on Python version we are using to run our code. There are some more elegant alternatives such as using future or six modules but this obligate us to include external packages and we want to minimzie that as much as possible. At least, for now.

https://python-future.org/compatible_idioms.html

Added new functions to ArtellaDrive to resolve paths

Resolving a path in ArtellaDrive terms means that, given path the server will return the path in local user workspace. Resolver can translates following types of paths:
- Handle URI paths: artella:handle-path
- File URI paths: file:///file-path
- File Paths: file-path.

Note that you can pass paths with env vars: $ARTELLA_FOLDER_ROOT/file-path. Environment variable will be automatically replace if it exists.

Added Artella Blender Addon implementation

This module contains Blender addon implementation. This addon manages the creation of the Artella menu/panel inside Blender. It supports both Blender 2.7 and 2.8:
- Blender 2.7: The menu is created in the top bar area of the application as a button with a custom menu that you can access.
- Blender 2.8: The menu is created in tools area of the 3D view. 

Maybe in the near future we will drop support for Blender 2.7
